BT 0 g /F2 16 Tf 171.6 750 Td (WHY MEAL PLANNING IS HARD WITH ADHD) Tj ET
q 0.5 G 1 w 100 740 m 512 740 l S Q
BT 0.2 g /F4 12 Tf 72 710 Td (If you struggle with food planning, you are not broken. Your brain works differently.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 13 Tf 72 680 Td (1. DECISION FATIGUE) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 11 Tf 90 660 Td (Every meal requires dozens of micro-decisions: what to eat, what to buy,) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 11 Tf 90 644 Td (how to prep, when to start. ADHD brains burn out on decisions fast.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 13 Tf 72 614 Td (2. EXECUTIVE DYSFUNCTION) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 11 Tf 90 594 Td (Knowing you need to eat and actually getting up to make food are) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 11 Tf 90 578 Td (two completely different things. The gap between intent and action is real.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 13 Tf 72 548 Td (3. BOREDOM WITH ROUTINE) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 11 Tf 90 528 Td (Traditional meal plans assume you can eat the same thing happily.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 11 Tf 90 512 Td (ADHD brains crave novelty - but also need structure. It's a paradox.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 13 Tf 72 482 Td (4. FORGETTING TO EAT) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 11 Tf 90 462 Td (Poor interoception means hunger signals get missed. You look up) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 11 Tf 90 446 Td (and it's 3pm and you haven't eaten. This isn't laziness - it's neurology.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 13 Tf 72 416 Td (5. HYPERFOCUS SKIPPING MEALS) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 11 Tf 90 396 Td (When you're locked into a task, eating feels like an impossible interruption.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 11 Tf 90 380 Td (Breaking hyperfocus to cook? That requires enormous energy.) Tj ET
q 0.92 g 72 330 468 55 re f Q
BT 0 g /F2 12 Tf 90 368 Td (THIS PLANNER'S APPROACH:) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 11 Tf 90 350 Td (Remove decisions. Make the easy path the default path.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 11 Tf 90 332 Td (Systems over willpower. Always.) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
